inputs.remark: 缺少 V2 follow up 数据。

logic_summary: Added V2 follow-up visit data derived from section 13.5 (Outcome), which details the 6-month post-treatment assessment including TFI/THI score reductions and persistent subjective symptoms.

value.collective_interpretation: Follow-up at 6 months showed clinically significant improvements in TFI and THI scores. Despite this, the patient reported persistent sound intolerance and pain with high-pitched sounds.

tests.name: Self-report scales
tests.result_summary: TFI decreased from 86/100 to 57/100; THI decreased from 70/100 to 44/100.

tests.name: Subjective report
tests.result_summary: Environmental sounds remained too loud; pain routinely produced by high-pitched sounds, horns, and sirens.
